Description: Sample of organic remains from inside a pot found in the NE-corner of the vestibule of the temple. Brown brittle small pieces of some organic substance that originally filled the pot. Broken into many small pieces.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), "Interior of pot. …this pot was found stopped north east corner of vestibule"
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
